To retrieve Oracle Unified Directory (OUD) user details using Python, you typically interact with it via LDAP protocol. This requires using the ldap3 library.

âœ… Prerequisites
Install ldap3 if not already:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install ldap3
Ensure you have:

OUD server hostname/IP

Port (typically 1389 for non-SSL, 1636 for SSL)

Bind DN (admin user DN)

Bind password

Base DN (from where to search users)

âœ… Sample Python Code to Fetch OUD User Details
python
Copy
Edit
from ldap3 import Server, Connection, ALL, SUBTREE

# === Configuration ===
OUD_SERVER = 'ldap://oud.example.com'  # or 'ldaps://oud.example.com' for SSL
OUD_PORT = 1389  # use 1636 for LDAPS
BIND_DN = 'cn=Directory Manager'  # or your specific admin DN
BIND_PASSWORD = 'your_password'
BASE_DN = 'dc=example,dc=com'
USER_FILTER = '(objectClass=inetOrgPerson)'  # You can filter further by uid or mail
ATTRIBUTES = ['uid', 'cn', 'sn', 'mail', 'employeeNumber']  # Customize this

# === Connect to OUD ===
server = Server(OUD_SERVER, port=OUD_PORT, get_info=ALL)
conn = Connection(server, user=BIND_DN, password=BIND_PASSWORD, auto_bind=True)

# === Search for Users ===
conn.search(
    search_base=BASE_DN,
    search_filter=USER_FILTER,
    search_scope=SUBTREE,
    attributes=ATTRIBUTES
)

# === Print Results ===
for entry in conn.entries:
    print(entry)

conn.unbind()
ðŸ”„ Example Output:
makefile
Copy
Edit
